    <body>
      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="M65104B1">
          <head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-M65104B1-headnote-1">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-M65104B1-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-M65104B1-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">A copy of this ingenious sally of Swift's happened to fall into the hands of Mr. James Stirling, a youthful poet of the county of Meath, who wrote the following lines in one of the blank leaves:&#13;</l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-M65104B1-headnote-2">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-M65104B1-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-M65104B1-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-M65104B1-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-M65104B1-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-M65104B1-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-1" n="1">While the <hi rend="italics">Dean</hi> with more wit than man ever wanted,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-2" n="2">Or than heav'n to any man else ever granted,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-3" n="3">Endeavours to prove, how the ancients in knowledge</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-4" n="4">Have excell'd our adepts of each <hi rend="italics">modern</hi> college;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-5" n="5">How heroes of old our chiefs are surpass'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-6" n="6">In each useful science, true learning, and taste:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-7" n="7">While thus he behaves, with more courage than manners,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-8" n="8">And fights for the foe, deserting our banners.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-9" n="9">While <hi rend="italics">Bentley</hi> and <hi rend="italics">Wotton</hi>, our champions, he foils;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-10" n="10">And wants neither <hi rend="italics">Temple's</hi> assistance, nor <hi rend="italics">Boyle's</hi>;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-11" n="11">In spite of his learning, fine reasons, and style,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-12" n="12">──Would you think it?── he favours our cause all the while:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-13" n="13">We raise by his conquest our glory the higher,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-14" n="14">And from our defeat to a triumph aspire:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-15" n="15">Our great <hi rend="italics">brother-modern</hi>, the <hi rend="italics">boast</hi> of our days,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-16" n="16">Unconscious, has gain'd for our party the bays:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-17" n="17"><hi rend="italics">St. James's</hi> old authors, so fam'd on each shelf,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-M65104B1-line-18" n="18">Are vanquish'd by what he has written himself.</l>
          </lg>
        </div>
      </div>
